60
00:04:56,517 --> 00:05:15,429
Subcommittee was formed to investigate and research the options for city council composition specifically to gather research and data on the current at large counselors versus a ward representation hybrid option and report back to the committee of the whole and tonight to do it in public.

61
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:31,734
The subcommittee did their due diligence in their research, utilizing city demographics, election results, citizen surveys, interviews, statewide comparisons, and other resources.

62
00:05:34,337 --> 00:05:41,284
The current city council is made up of members, and each one of those members

63
00:05:43,186 --> 00:05:47,336
is elected on an at large basis, which means the entire city votes for them.

64
00:05:48,378 --> 00:05:50,382
The term currently is two years.

65
00:05:53,602 --> 00:05:54,743
So we looked at three options.

66
00:05:54,863 --> 00:06:02,632
One was to do nothing and just continue as is with the seven member city council, same term, same everything.

67
00:06:04,214 --> 00:06:13,344
Option two was to transition to a hybrid ward representative council, which means that each ward would have a representative.

68
00:06:13,364 --> 00:06:14,685
You wanna click one more, I think it adds.

69
00:06:15,646 --> 00:06:20,428
So we have eight boards in the city, which means there would be eight ward reps.

70
00:06:20,908 --> 00:06:23,509
And then to balance it off, there would be some at-large reps.

71
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:25,009
That's where the hybrid piece is.

72
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:30,391
So you're looking at a total of 11 or even as much as 13 or more.

73
00:06:31,372 --> 00:06:40,935
And the final option we had was to just simply increase the number of city councilors all still being elected in the at-large method of election.

74
00:06:43,164 --> 00:06:46,385
