How one question we looked at is how representative is city council school committee, the mayor, when compared to the population of Medford as a whole.

79
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:29,033
So this first slide shows you overall demographics for the city.

80
00:07:29,053 --> 00:07:38,460
We have approximately 60,000 residents, and our population has been increasing since 2010 or even earlier.

81
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:41,982
We're equally divided between men and women.

82
00:07:42,843 --> 00:07:52,150
About 23% has been born in another country, and approximately one out of three residents speak a language other than English in the home.

83
00:07:52,970 --> 00:08:02,061
In Medford we have a high proportion of people who may need language services in the city or who speak another language with their family.

84
00:08:03,102 --> 00:08:09,470
For people who are under 65 approximately 5% identify as having a disability.

85
00:08:10,551 --> 00:08:18,774
Income-wise, almost 8% live in poverty, and about 20% have incomes above $200,000.

86
00:08:19,274 --> 00:08:25,437
We're also pretty evenly divided between homeowners and renters.

87
00:08:25,457 --> 00:08:30,859
Approximately 55% of our housing units are owner-occupied.

88
00:08:31,579 --> 00:08:38,462
This pie chart shows you just the age breakdown with, I can see it better on yours,

89
00:08:39,002 --> 00:08:49,591
But with the majority of adults being 45 to 24 years old.

90
00:08:51,092 --> 00:08:57,858
And this is all data from the 2020 census and also data that the city of Medford put together for their last budget.

91
00:09:00,776 --> 00:09:14,262
Then I just want to recognize that the city's Office of Planning and Development and sustainability helped me get data by ward because one question we had is, do we have some words that are more diverse than other words.

92
00:09:14,763 --> 00:09:17,344
And so this chart here shows you by ward.

93
00:09:20,545 --> 00:09:23,627
the racial makeup of each ward.

94
00:09:24,107 --> 00:09:39,274
And you can see that some wards are predominantly white, where Ward 7, which is where if you vote, you would be voting Mystic Towers or McGlynn, is a minority majority ward with 51% non-white and 49% white.

95
00:09:39,294 --> 00:09:39,334
Oh.

96
00:09:49,096 --> 00:09:53,857
So just so you know, I'm manning both at Zoom and letting people in and presenting.

