264
00:31:03,092 --> 00:31:04,213
My first question was,

265
00:31:05,548 --> 00:31:14,300
no one ran in a ward, then that ward would not have a rep, no one, you know, ran or no one chose to represent.

266
00:31:15,502 --> 00:31:19,167
Well, that basically wouldn't mean we won less counselor, correct?

267
00:31:22,764 --> 00:31:27,970
Yeah, there are specific provisions for when a ward does not present a candidate into the election.

268
00:31:29,912 --> 00:31:36,719
It will be added to the charter, but basically it's, you find somebody.

269
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,082
And pretty much that's what the,

270
00:31:41,204 --> 00:31:45,348
Massachusetts tells you if nobody runs from your ward, find somebody.

271
00:31:46,690 --> 00:31:53,356
So once we go to ward representation, that will be part of it.

272
00:31:54,598 --> 00:31:56,740
Every ward would have representation.

273
00:31:56,760 --> 00:32:02,866
There's also provisions, as Melva says, for when a ward rep moves out of the ward,

274
00:32:04,347 --> 00:32:08,750
So there are a lot of provisions that have to come into play when you're making this kind of decision.

275
00:32:08,830 --> 00:32:17,935
But certainly to your question, if a ward does not present a candidate, you go back to the ward and you find somebody.

276
00:32:19,276 --> 00:32:20,177
OK, understood.

277
00:32:21,217 --> 00:32:21,538
Oh, sorry.

278
00:32:21,918 --> 00:32:23,819
Who's been giving us guidance on some of these questions.

279
00:32:23,839 --> 00:32:25,080
That question's come up before.

280
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:30,963
And their impression was that this very rarely happens, that there isn't a ward where no one runs, typically.

281
00:32:35,316 --> 00:32:35,917
Okay, thank you.

282
00:32:35,977 --> 00:32:44,263
And then my other question is, you posted the survey link, which I've replied to, and I've passed it along to other people.

283
00:32:44,283 --> 00:32:46,785
