301
00:34:02,529 --> 00:34:02,930
Thank you.

302
00:34:04,291 --> 00:34:04,552
Maureen.

303
00:34:08,780 --> 00:34:09,500
Yes, thank you.

304
00:34:09,700 --> 00:34:11,300
And first of all, thanks to the committee.

305
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:18,162
This is great, and your presentation was really wonderful, very clear, and I appreciate the work that you've done.

306
00:34:19,282 --> 00:34:28,464
My question, I am from West Medford, and my question is, what is the thinking behind the number of three to four at-large members?

307
00:34:29,384 --> 00:34:30,484
Why that number?

308
00:34:31,264 --> 00:34:36,365
I don't know if it's based on other cities or towns, but that's what I'd like to know.

309
00:34:38,112 --> 00:34:41,777
Yeah, so my understanding is that you need an odd number of people on the council.

310
00:34:41,857 --> 00:34:50,029
So if we went to eight, if we went to representing all eight wards, we would need at least three to make that odd number.

311
00:34:50,049 --> 00:34:51,731
Not sure why it's not one.

312
00:34:52,693 --> 00:34:53,554
It could be one, yeah.

313
00:34:58,015 --> 00:35:10,198
In looking at making it a candidate-friendly election, most cities and towns choose to have three at large as opposed to five people fighting for one seat.

314
00:35:10,718 --> 00:35:11,838
So you don't really have an option.

315
00:35:11,858 --> 00:35:22,480
When you go to the ward representation at eight for us, and we're really changing it as an act of the statehouse and the Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

316
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:24,200
But that could be done as well.

317
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:25,961
But for our purposes,

318
00:35:27,521 --> 00:35:34,786
You have to have an odd number, like Danielle says, and also we think three is very reasonable.

319
00:35:35,087 --> 00:35:42,191
Some folks have an opinion of five, which really grows the council, but it's a matter of having an odd number.

320
00:35:44,353 --> 00:35:45,914
Great, thank you very much.

321
00:35:46,694 --> 00:35:54,760
I really think that the hybrid model seems to be one that would best serve the people of Medford, so thank you again for the presentation.

322
00:36:01,383 --> 00:36:01,723
Steve?

323
00:36:01,743 --> 00:36:05,424
Hi, thank you.

324
00:36:05,504 --> 00:36:06,324
I'm Steve Schnapp.

325
00:36:06,465 --> 00:36:10,046
I live in Medford Square on Hillside Ave.

326
00:36:10,946 --> 00:36:13,046
